  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641914074770-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641914074770-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641914074770-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641914074770-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641914074770-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641914081502-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641914081502-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641914081502-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641914081502-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641914081502-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your <strong>cumin seeds</strong>, <strong>black mustard seeds</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant add the <strong>vegetable stock</strong> and <strong>spinach </strong>and cook, covered, for 7-8 min or until the butternut squash is tender – this is your <strong>spiced spinach & butternut squash mix</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641914092360-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641914092360-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641914092360-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641914092360-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641914092360-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Melt 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> in a pot over a medium heat, then add your <strong>curry powder </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g] </span><strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Add 250ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml] </span><strong>milk </strong>gradually and whisk for 4-5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains, then remove from the heat, stir through <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and<strong> </strong>season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your<strong> curried</strong> <strong>béchamel</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1641914135781-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1641914135781-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1641914135781-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1641914135781-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1641914135781-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Layer some of the <strong>spiced spinach & butternut squash mix</strong> over the bottom of an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong>, then top with some of your <strong>lasagne sheets</strong>, being careful not to overlap the pasta</p><p>Repeat this process until you end up with a final layer of lasagne sheets (you may need to layer differently depending on the size of your dish)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641914182294-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641914182294-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641914182294-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641914182294-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641914182294-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top the lasagne sheets with the <strong>curried</strong> <strong>béchamel</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over your <strong>nigella seeds</strong> and the <strong>remaining grated cheese</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 30-35 min or until the pasta is cooked through and everything's golden – this is your <strong>curried</strong> <strong>squash & spinach lasagne</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641914200626-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641914200626-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641914200626-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641914200626-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641914200626-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> baby leaf salad</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p><p>Add your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> to a bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and stir it all together – this is your <strong>salad</strong> <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Once the lasagne is almost cooked, add the <strong>baby leaf salad</strong> to the salad dressing and give it a gentle mix up – this is your <strong>salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1641914207384-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1641914207384-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1641914207384-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1641914207384-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1641914207384-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>curried</strong> <strong>squash & spinach lasagne </strong>with the <strong>salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
